  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a concave mirror facing to the right with its principal axis shown as a dash line to the right. Two vertical arrows, one pointing up and labeled Object and the second pointing down and labeled Image are located on the same point on the principal axis to the right of the mirror. The distance between the mirror and the object and the image is labeled d sub 0. A distance labeled d sub o new, that is greater than d sub 0, is also indicated. A note indicates the figure is not drawn to scale.\" src=\"/images/36402b2e4e2ce34c9920b99628c9def9.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">An object is located a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d sub 0\"><math alttext=\"d sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>d</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> from a concave mirror, as shown in the figure. The image formed by the mirror is located the same distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d sub 0\"><math alttext=\"d sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>d</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> from the mirror, as indicated. The object is then moved a short distance farther from the mirror to a new position that is a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d sub o new, end sub, is greater than d sub 0\"><math alttext=\"d sub o new, end sub, is greater than d sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>d</mi><mtext>o-new</mtext></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>d</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> from the mirror. Which of the following is a correct relation for the distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d sub i new, end sub\"><math alttext=\"d sub i new, end sub\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>d</mi><mtext>i-new</mtext></msub></math></span></span> between the new image location and the mirror?</p>\n",
